  "format": "Sean Fennessey and Amanda Dobbins hand the ballot to Wesley Morris and rebuild the Oscars from scratch: nine invented categories, then all-new nominees in the six biggest races. Atlantics, Rob Morgan, and American Factory go home with statues that don't exist.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The State of the 2020 Oscars",
      "note": "before the alternate ceremony",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Parasite",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "No precedent for a film like this getting this close to a Best Picture win, unimaginable even in September."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Irishman",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "One of a couple of expensive, studio-defying swings that pushed this year's slate up."
        },
        {
          "title": "Marriage Story",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "The other one: money no other studio would have spent."
        },
        {
          "title": "Joker",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "A highly unusual movie to have been made, marketed, and rewarded the way it was."
        },
        {
          "title": "1917",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Loved but the definition of an 'Oscar movie'; a win would feel like a message being sent."
        }
